'''Long Branch''' is a  commuter rail station on the , located in , , and serving Long Branch,  and .
The current Long Branch station was built in 1988 when electrification was completed to this point and replaced an older depot. The ticket office and vending machines are located in the glass building on the center of the high platform. 
It is the terminus of both diesel and electric service; a transfer is needed to continue the journey.  Located in the heart of downtown Long Branch between grade crossings at Bath and Westwood Avenues, the station features a single high level island platform. Passengers arriving from Bay Head destined for New York platform on the eastbound track and must change trains across the platform to an electric local or express train. Long Branch Station features a large 16-track storage and maintenance yard for all New York-bound electric trains arriving and waiting to depart.
